    Scope and Contents
Justice and the Social Order Program course files (1973-1977) consists of syllabi, articles and news clippings, lecture materials, bibliographies, course descriptions and memos for courses taught by or in association with Professor Larry Golden.  The Jusitce and the Social Order Program sought to provide clarity and understanding of  problems in todays society:  poverty, violence, racism, exploitation, discrimination and alienation.  Program was terminated following the 1977 Spring semester.  
  
